<inglise>Chapter 4 </inglise>
<eesti>Toimingupiirangud </eesti>
<inglise>Procedural Restrictions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 21. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 21. </inglise>
<eesti>Toimingupiirangu m&otilde;iste </eesti>
<inglise>Definition of procedural restrictions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Toimingupiiranguna k&auml;sitatakse k&auml;esolevas seaduses keeldu teha korruptiivse tulu saamist v&otilde;imaldavaid toiminguid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) For the purposes of this Act, a procedural restriction means a prohibition to perform acts which enable to receive income derived from corrupt practices. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Toimingupiirangut ei kohaldata tegevusele, mille tulemusel saadakse tulu aktsiatelt v&otilde;i &auml;ri&uuml;hingu osadelt, kui seaduses ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Procedural restrictions do not apply to activities as a result of which income on shares of a company is received, unless otherwise provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>Ametiisik v&otilde;ib saada tulu ka autoritasuna, patendituluna, intressidena hoiustelt, rendile v&otilde;i teiste isikute kasutusse antud kinnisasjalt, honorarina tr&uuml;kis v&otilde;i elektroonilises ajakirjanduses avaldatud t&ouml;&ouml;de eest, samuti muud tulu, mis ei eelda selle saaja t&ouml;&ouml;tamist teise isiku majandusliku kasu soodustamiseks, kui seaduses ei ole s&auml;testatud teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>An official may also receive income as royalties, revenue from patents, interest on deposits, on immovables which are subjected to commercial lease or use by other persons, fee for the works published in print or electronic media, and other income which does not presume the employment of the recipient thereof to promote the economic benefit of another person, unless otherwise provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 22. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 22. </inglise>
<eesti>Tasu v&otilde;i suurema tasu v&otilde;tmise keeld </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibition on acceptance of remuneration or more than adequate remuneration </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametiisikul, kes peab tasuta osutama teenuseid v&otilde;i langetama otsuseid, on keelatud n&otilde;uda v&otilde;i vastu v&otilde;tta nende eest tasu rahas, loonustasu v&otilde;i mingi vastuteenena. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official who is required to provide services or make decisions without charge shall not demand or accept remuneration therefor in money, in kind or as a favour. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametiisikul, kes peab osutama teenuseid ametlikus korras rahas kindlaksm&auml;&auml;ratud tasu eest, on keelatud n&otilde;uda v&otilde;i vastu v&otilde;tta nende eest tariifides v&otilde;i hinnakirjades toodud tasust erinevat tasu. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official who is required to provide services pursuant to the official procedure for a specific remuneration in money, shall not demand or accept remuneration therefor different from the remuneration set out in the rates or price lists. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 23. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 23. </inglise>
<eesti>Altk&auml;emaksust teatamise kohustus </eesti>
<inglise>Duty to give notification of bribery </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametiisik on kohustatud igast talle teatavaks saanud altk&auml;emaksu pakkumisest, andmisest v&otilde;i v&otilde;tmisest kirjalikult teatama vahetule &uuml;lemusele v&otilde;i asutuse juhile ja politseile. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official is required to notify the immediate superior or head of the agency and the police in writing of any offering, giving or acceptance of a bribe which becomes known to him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Altk&auml;emaksu andmisest, v&otilde;tmisest v&otilde;i pakkumisest k&auml;esolevas seaduses s&auml;testatud korras teatamata j&auml;tmine on aluseks avalikus teenistuses oleva ametiisiku teenistusest vabastamisele. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Failure to give notification of an offering, giving or acceptance of a bribe pursuant to the procedure provided for in this Act shall be the basis for the release of the official in the public service from service. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 24. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 24. </inglise>
<eesti>Keelatud tehingud </eesti>
<inglise>Prohibited transactions </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametiisikul on keelatud sooritada tehinguid iseendaga v&otilde;i muid sarnase iseloomuga v&otilde;i huvide konfliktiga seotud tehinguid. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official shall not engage in self-dealing, or conclude transactions of similar nature or involving a conflict of interest. </inglise>
<eesti>Samuti ei v&otilde;i ta volitada oma alluvaid tegema vastavaid tehinguid tema asemel. </eesti>
<inglise>He or she shall not authorise persons subordinate to him or her to perform such transactions instead of him or her. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Tehingutena iseendaga, mis on keelatud, k&auml;sitatakse muuhulgas: </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Self-dealing, which is prohibited, means inter alia the following: </inglise>
<eesti>1) ametiasutuse poolt tema k&auml;tte usaldatud vara osas tehingute s&otilde;lmimist iseenda v&otilde;i juriidilise isikuga, mille aktsiad v&otilde;i osad kuuluvad kas t&auml;ielikult v&otilde;i osaliselt talle v&otilde;i tema l&auml;hisugulastele ja -h&otilde;imlastele v&otilde;i mille juhtkonna v&otilde;i otsuseid tegeva organi liige ta on; </eesti>
<inglise>1) concluding, with regard to property entrusted to him or her by an agency, transactions with oneself or a legal person the shares of which belong either wholly or partially to him or her, his or her close relatives or close relatives by marriage, or a board or decision-making body of which he or she is a member; </inglise>
<eesti>2) riigiasutust tehingus esindama &otilde;igustatud isikuna asjaomase ametiasutuse kaudu tehingute tegemist riigiga v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse asutust tehingus esindama &otilde;igustatud isikuna asjaomase ametiasutuse kaudu tehingute tegemist kohaliku omavalitsusega; </eesti>
<inglise>2) concluding, as a person entitled to represent a state agency in transactions, transactions with the state through an administrative agency concerned, or concluding, as a person entitled to represent a local government agency in transactions, transactions with a local government through an administrative agency concerned; </inglise>
<eesti>3) riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse esindajana varaliste tehingute tegemist teiste t&ouml;&ouml;andjatega, kelle teenistuses ta on; </eesti>
<inglise>3) concluding, as a representative of the state or a local government, property transactions with other employers in whose employment he or she is; </inglise>
<eesti>4) riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse esindajana varaliste tehingute tegemist k&auml;esoleva seaduse &sect; 25 l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud juriidiliste isikutega; </eesti>
<inglise>4) concluding, as a representative of the state or a local government, property transactions with legal persons specified in subsection 25 (1) of this Act; </inglise>
<eesti>5) riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse esindajana varaliste tehingute tegemist mittetulundus&uuml;hingu v&otilde;i erakonnaga, mille liige ta on; </eesti>
<inglise>5) concluding, as a representative of the state or a local government, property transactions with a non-profit association or political party of which he or she is a member; </inglise>
<eesti>6) riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse esindajana varaliste tehingute tegemist selle t&ouml;&ouml;andja, &auml;ri&uuml;hingu, mittetulundus&uuml;hingu v&otilde;i erakonnaga, kelle tegevust ta kontrollib; </eesti>
<inglise>6) concluding, as a representative of the state or a local government, property transactions with an employer, company, non-profit association or political party over the activities of which he or she exercises supervision; </inglise>
<eesti>7) riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse esindajana varaliste tehingute tegemist oma l&auml;hisugulaste, -h&otilde;imlaste v&otilde;i iseendaga. </eesti>
<inglise>7) concluding, as a representative of the state or a local government, property transactions with one's close relatives, close relatives by marriage or oneself. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 2 s&auml;testatud piiranguid riigi v&otilde;i kohaliku omavalitsuse esindajate kohta kohaldatakse ka avalik-&otilde;igusliku juriidilise isiku esindajale. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) The restrictions concerning the representatives of the state or a local government provided for in subsection (2) of this section also apply to the representative of a legal person in public law. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 s&auml;testatud keeldu rikkudes tehtud tehing on t&uuml;hine. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) Transactions concluded in violation of the prohibitions provided for in subsection (1) of this section are void. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 25. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 25. </inglise>
<eesti>Huvide konflikt </eesti>
<inglise>Conflict of interest </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Huvide konfliktiga on tegemist juhul, kui ametiisik peab tegema oma t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i teenistuskohustuste raames otsuse v&otilde;i osalema sellise otsuse tegemises, mis oluliselt m&otilde;jutab tema enda, tema l&auml;hisugulaste v&otilde;i -h&otilde;imlaste v&otilde;i juriidiliste isikute majandushuve, kui juriidiliseks isikuks on: </eesti>
<inglise>(1) A conflict of interest occurs if an official, in the course of his or her duties of employment, is required to make a decision or participate in the making of a decision which significantly influences the economic interests of the official, his or her close relatives or close relatives by marriage or legal persons, if the legal person is: </inglise>
<eesti>1) t&auml;is&uuml;hing, mille osanik on ametiisik v&otilde;i tema l&auml;hisugulane v&otilde;i -h&otilde;imlane; </eesti>
<inglise>1) a general partnership, the partner of which the official, his or her close relative or close relative by marriage is; </inglise>
<eesti>2) usaldus&uuml;hing, mille t&auml;isosanik v&otilde;i usaldusosanik on ametiisik v&otilde;i tema l&auml;hisugulane v&otilde;i -h&otilde;imlane; </eesti>
<inglise>2) a limited partnership, the general partner or limited partner of which the official, his or her close relative or close relative by marriage is; </inglise>
<eesti>3) osa&uuml;hing, mille osanik v&otilde;i juhatuse v&otilde;i n&otilde;ukogu liige on ametiisik v&otilde;i tema l&auml;hisugulane v&otilde;i -h&otilde;imlane; </eesti>
<inglise>3) a private limited company, the shareholder or member of the management board or supervisory board of which the official, his or her close relative or close relative by marriage is; </inglise>
<eesti>4) aktsiaselts, mille aktsion&auml;r v&otilde;i juhatuse v&otilde;i n&otilde;ukogu liige on ametiisik v&otilde;i tema l&auml;hisugulane v&otilde;i -h&otilde;imlane; </eesti>
<inglise>4) a public limited company, the shareholder or member of the management board or supervisory board of which the official, his or her close relative or close relative by marriage is; </inglise>
<eesti>5) tulundus&uuml;histu, mille juhatuse v&otilde;i revisjonikomisjoni liige on ametiisik v&otilde;i tema l&auml;hisugulane v&otilde;i -h&otilde;imlane; </eesti>
<inglise>5) a commercial association, the member of the management board or audit committee of which the official, his or her close relative or close relative by marriage is; </inglise>
<eesti>6) muu era&otilde;iguslik juriidiline isik, mille juht- v&otilde;i j&auml;relevalveorgani liige on ametiisik v&otilde;i tema l&auml;hisugulane v&otilde;i -h&otilde;imlane. </eesti>
<inglise>6) other legal person in private law, the member of the directing or supervisory body of which the official, his or her close relative or close relative by marriage is. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametiisik, kelle &uuml;lesanne on osaleda k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud &uuml;hisotsuse tegemises, on kohustatud sellest viivitamata teatama asjaomasele organile ja oma vahetule &uuml;lemusele v&otilde;i teenistusse v&otilde;tmise v&otilde;i ametisse nimetamise &otilde;igusega isikule v&otilde;i organile ning loobuma otsuse tegemisest. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official whose duty is to participate in the making of common decisions specified in subsection (1) of this section is required to notify promptly a body concerned and his or her immediate superior or a person or body with the employment or appointment authority thereof and forego the making of the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>Isik v&otilde;i organ, kes on m&auml;&auml;ranud ametiisiku &uuml;hisotsuseid tegeva organi liikmeks, v&otilde;ib m&auml;&auml;rata teise isiku ametiisiku &uuml;hekordseks asendamiseks. </eesti>
<inglise>The person or body who has designated an official as a member of a body making common decisions, may designate another person for the one-time substitution of the official. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) Ametiisik, kelle p&auml;devuses on teha k&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 nimetatud otsuseid ainuisikuliselt, on kohustatud ennast otsuse tegemisest taandama ning teatama huvide konfliktist oma vahetule &uuml;lemusele, kes peab otsuse tegemiseks m&auml;&auml;rama teise ametiisiku. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) An official who is competent to make decisions specified in subsection (1) of this section solely, is required to remove himself or herself from making the decision and notify his or her immediate superior of a conflict of interest; the immediate superior shall designate another official to make the decision. </inglise>
<eesti>(4) Selles paragrahvis ei k&auml;sitata &otilde;igustloovat &uuml;ldakti otsusena. </eesti>
<inglise>(4) In this section, a decision does not mean legislation of general application. </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 26. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 26. </inglise>
<eesti>Kingituste vastuv&otilde;tmise piirang </eesti>
<inglise>Restriction on acceptance of gifts </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametiisikul on keelatud seoses oma t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i teenistuskohustustega m&otilde;jutada isikuid tegema temale v&otilde;i tema l&auml;hisugulastele v&otilde;i -h&otilde;imlastele kingitusi v&otilde;i muid soodustusi. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official shall not solicit, in connection with his or her duties of employment, gifts or other benefits made or granted by persons to him or her, his or her close relatives or close relatives by marriage. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametiisik ei v&otilde;i vastu v&otilde;tta kingitusi ega n&otilde;ustuda soodustustega, mis on m&auml;&auml;ratud temale endale v&otilde;i tema l&auml;hisugulastele v&otilde;i -h&otilde;imlastele ning mille vastuv&otilde;tmine v&otilde;ib otse v&otilde;i kaudselt m&otilde;jutada tema t&ouml;&ouml;- v&otilde;i teenistuskohustuste erapooletut t&auml;itmist. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) An official shall not accept gifts or consent to the benefits which are made or granted to him or her, his or her close relatives or close relatives by marriage, and the acceptance of which may directly or indirectly influence the impartial performance of his or her duties of employment or service. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;igetes 1 ja 2 s&auml;testatud piirangute rikkumisega saadud kingitused kuuluvad vastava ametiisiku t&ouml;&ouml;andjale, kui rahvusvahelisest tavast v&otilde;i diplomaatilisest etiketist ei tulene teisiti. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Gifts received in violation of the restrictions provided for in subsections (1) and (2) of this section shall belong to the employer of the corresponding official, unless otherwise provided by an international custom or diplomatic etiquette. </inglise>
<eesti>5. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 5 </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus </eesti>
<inglise>Liability </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27. </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27. </inglise>
<eesti>Vastutus korruptsioonivastase seaduse rikkumise eest </eesti>
<inglise>Liability for violation of Anti-corruption Act </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Ametiisik, kes on toime pannud korruptiivse teo v&otilde;i v&otilde;tnud seadusevastast tasu v&otilde;i loonud korruptsiooniohtlikud suhted v&otilde;i rikkunud t&ouml;&ouml;koha-, tegevus- v&otilde;i toimingupiiranguid v&otilde;i j&auml;tnud majanduslike huvide deklaratsiooni t&auml;htp&auml;evaks esitamata v&otilde;i esitanud deklaratsioonis mittet&auml;ielikke v&otilde;i valeandmeid, v&otilde;etakse vastutusele seadusega s&auml;testatud korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) An official who commits an act of corruption or unlawfully accepts remuneration or has relationships involving a risk of corruption or violates the restrictions on employment and activities or procedural restrictions or fails to submit a declaration of economic interests by the due date or submits incomplete or false information in the declaration shall be brought to justice pursuant to the procedure provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Asutuse juht ja ametiisik, kellele on pandud deklaratsioonihoidja &uuml;lesanded, kannavad nende &uuml;lesannete t&auml;itmataj&auml;tmise v&otilde;i mittekohase t&auml;itmise, samuti deklaratsioonide sisu seadusevastase avalikustamise eest distsiplinaar-, haldus- v&otilde;i kriminaalvastutust. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) The head of an agency and an official who are assigned the duties of a depositary of declaration shall bear disciplinary, administrative or criminal liability for failure to perform or unsatisfactory performance of duties and for unlawful disclosure of the contents of declarations. </inglise>
<eesti>(3) K&auml;esoleva paragrahvi l&otilde;ikes 1 loetletud teod on aluseks ametiisiku teenistusest v&otilde;i ametikohalt vabastamiseks, v&auml;lja arvatud eriseadustes s&auml;testatud juhud. </eesti>
<inglise>(3) Acts listed in subsection (1) of this section shall constitute the basis for the release of an official from service or office, except in the cases provided for in specific Acts. </inglise>
<eesti>(07.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.03.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 58, 357) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.06.2001 entered into force 03.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 58, 357) </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 27 (1). </eesti>
<inglise>&sect; 27 (1). </inglise>
<eesti>Korruptiivse teoga tekitatud kahju h&uuml;vitamine </eesti>
<inglise>Compensation for damage caused by acts of corruption </inglise>
<eesti>(1) Isikutel, kes on saanud kahju ametiisiku korruptiivse teo tagaj&auml;rjel, on &otilde;igus n&otilde;uda kahju h&uuml;vitamist seadusega s&auml;testatud alustel ja korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(1) Persons who have suffered damage as a result of an act of corruption of an official have the right to demand compensation for such damage on the bases and pursuant to the procedure provided by law. </inglise>
<eesti>(2) Ametiisikult n&otilde;utakse tekitatud kahju sisse regressi korras. </eesti>
<inglise>(2) Damages shall be claimed from an official by way of recourse. </inglise>
<eesti>(07.06.2001 j&otilde;ust.03.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 58, 357) </eesti>
<inglise>(07.06.2001 entered into force 03.07.2001 - RT I 2001, 58, 357) </inglise>
<eesti>6. peat&uuml;kk </eesti>
<inglise>Chapter 6 </inglise>
<eesti>Rakenduss&auml;tted </eesti>
<inglise>Implementing Provisions </inglise>
<eesti>&sect; 28. </eesti>
